social_posts.post_text: SOLD! The Triassic-Five has left Long Beach and is onto its next adventure in the frigid Midwest.  Don’t be shocked or sad, all my cars are always available for sale if you’re interested. Selling them allows others to enjoy them and frees me up with funds and space to build the next one- which is exactly what I intend to do.  Thank you, everyone, for your love and support on this car, it came to me as a derelict carcass and has far surpassed any level of popularity and success I could have ever imagined.  BTW, the new owner, Terry, is a HW collector, too, and will drive the snot out of this car as it was built to be. You might even see it at the next Nationals event.  #triassicfive #triassicfivegasser #gasser #hotrod #sold #1955chevy #55chevy #chevy #newadventures

Just your typical Saturday morning engine pull helping a good friend, Tom, remove the old 413 wedge to make room for a new 700hp 440 wedge which will be coming soon.  And yes, doing this makes me miss my 55. #gasser #plymouth #wedge #413 #440 #hotrod #wrenching #saturday #morning
The next project…. A gasser build for my father

Introducing the next (mild) project- a gasser build for my father. After selling my Triassic-Five he said I could build him a car, and so I shall.  His first car was a ‘56, and he hasn’t had many, if any, fun cars since. This will be a mild build- something fun to cruise in and have the look without the required maintenance of a high power ride. I also want to get it to him sooner than later as summers are short where he lives and every year counts.  Stay tuned.  #chevrolet @chevrolet #chevy #gasser #project #next #anotherone #hotrod #disturbingtheneighbors

The old engine is out, and I made a huge mess out of my garage and driveway, too. Note the hack/ modification made to the cherry picker I borrowed. Even with the bumper off it wasn’t long enough to reach, and while it worked for me please don’t try that at home 😂 #56 #chevy #chevrolet #gasser #hotrod #engineremoval #enginepull #toolhack #badidea #wednesday #disturbingtheneighbors

I just can’t leave well enough alone. Less than a week ago I drove this car into my garage, and now it’s all apart. It’s a good thing I’m doing this, though, as the front end bushings were shot, and the aftermarket disc brake kit was improperly installed- resulting in a potentially dangerous situation.  Not to worry, this car will be up and running better than it ever has in 2023.  Stay tuned.  #1956 #56 #56chevy #chevy #chevrolet @chevrolet @chevroletperformance #gasser #hotrod #upgrade #saturday #weekend #teardown #rebuild #disturbingtheneighbors

Small updates on the ‘56- the front end is back together and has a better gasser-ish stance, the rear is now out and will be sent out Monday to be refreshed, and I added a clutch pedal back in this car (some previous owner cut it off). I also picked up the T56 for this, too.  #1956 #56 #chevy #chevrolet #gasser #hotrod #hotrodding #saturday #weekend #upgrade #fun #disturbingtheneighbors

Some photo updates on my father’s’56.  The front and rear suspension are rebuilt, as is the steering system.  I made new door panels and painted the dash adding a turned gold metal decal on them both, new hand bend fuel and brake lines underneath as well as an electric fuel pump added into the tank.  New side window glass/ felt/ seals.  Still planning to be finished this year.  #1956 #chevrolet #gasser #hotrod #homebuilt #fabrication #saturday #disturbingtheneighbors

Had a blast today “at work” visiting the Galpin Speed Shop up in Van Nuys and checking out the cool cars owned by Beau Boeckmann and taken care of/ restored by Dave Shuten.  It’s an amazing one of a kind collection of famous and iconic cars, NOS speed parts and Automobilia and Dave does amazing work taking care of it all. Be sure to give him a follow if you don’t already. #galpinspeedshop #galpinautosports @galpinspeedshop @daveshuten #hotrods #kustom #cars #hotrod @beauboeckmann

I just returned from a two week trip to both Jakarta and Manila attending Hot Wheels Legends events and diecast collector dinner events at each stop and finally got to see both of our MIDC and PTMI plants in Jakarta, too.  I caught up with many friends and made some new ones as well and was spoiled with so many goodies that I had to buy a second suitcase just to bring it all home!  It would be tough to thank everybody individually but please know that I am deeply grateful and humbled for the generosity and kindness that everyone has shown me on this trip and will gladly come back the next opportunity I’m given.  Sincerely, thank you 🙏  @hotwheelslegends #hotwheelslegends #jakarta #manila #ide #pdcgroup
Sunday night hotrodding- suspension upgrades for the GTO
Updates on the 56 gasser….

Thank you @fitech_efi @schmidt_jerms @fitech_mike for tuning the ‘56 and getting it to run right… something outside of my skill set.  It’s about 340 hp to the wheels which should be enough to put miles of smiles on my father’s face (disregard the torque number it’s not correct) The car is almost done and ready to be delivered now.  Still need to reinstall the hood, but I really don’t want to, ha ha #fitech #fitechefi #dynotuned #dyno #dynomometer #chevy #gasser #chevrolet @chevroletperformance

Mission accomplished!  The ‘56 is now a resident of New York and my father is already enjoying driving it despite the weather.  #1956chevy #56chevy #chevy #gasser #hotrod #homebuilt #chevrolet @chevroletperformance

There’s a story to these car keys. They were the keys to the first car my father ever owned back in high school- also a 56 Chevy. He had to sell it but kept the keys and gave them to me when I was a kid. I kept them all these years and had the ignition rekeyed to use this and I gave them back to him this weekend.  #1956chevy #56chevy #chevy #gasser #keys #gift
